Package: welschAdEnet
Type: Package
Title: Welsch Adaptive Elastic-Net for Robust Sparse Regression
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("R. K.", "Mishra", email = "rkmishra.stat@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits a high-breakdown estimator for sparse linear regression
    that couples a redescending Welsch loss with an adaptive elastic-net
    penalty, solved by a first-order proximal Adam scheme and tuned by a
    robust Bayesian information criterion. The Welsch loss downweights
    large residuals to zero, giving resistance to both vertical outliers
    and high-leverage points, while the adaptive elastic-net penalty
    produces exact variable selection and grouped shrinkage of correlated
    predictors. Also includes several competing penalized robust-regression
    losses (squared, absolute, Huber, Tukey) fit with the same solver, and
    tools for reproducing a simulation study under vertical-outlier and
    leverage contamination regimes. Methods are described in Mishra (2026,
    manuscript in preparation).
